      "body": "Hi @1286482110. This library is not a general purpose crypto library and therefore does not expose field or group operations. If you only want to experiment, you've apparently figured out how to get it to work. Alternatively, you can play with `tests.c` and run the binary with `make && ./tests`. If you want to implement your own cryptographic scheme, the best way is to fork the library and add a custom module.",
